  "text": "Somewhat surprisingly, the intensive lifestyle intervention and the close follow-up were equally effective with respect to glucose tolerance and GDM in the current study. High-risk pregnant women may be particularly receptive to lifestyle advice. On the other hand a part of women are not able to change their lifestyle or the maintenance of applied eating or physical activity habits are short sighted even during pregnancy. Small group differences at randomization may also have affected the results. Prepregnancy weight in the lifestyle intervention The three-factor eating questionnaire [CITATION_1] . f Gestational diabetes mellitus. group tended to be higher compared with the close follow-up group, and all women weighing over 100 kg were in the intervention group. The women in the close follow-up group tended to have a higher educational status (p = 0.080).",
